FBIS4-19181 "drweu072_q_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-072 Daily Report 12 Apr 1994 TURKEY Croatia's Granic Comments on Balkan Conflict Croatia's Granic Comments on Balkan Conflict TA1304133594 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 2000 GMT 12 Apr 94 TA1304133594 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network Turkish BFN [Text] President Suleyman Demirel has received Mate Granic, Croatian deputy prime minister and foreign minister, who is on an official visit in Ankara, at the Cankaya Mansion. According to a statement issued by the Press Center of the President's Office, Granic thanked Turkey for its support and constructive stand in solving the problems associated with the dissolution of Yugoslavia. Granic stated that despite the swift implementation of the Croatian-Bosnian agreement signed in Washington, the Bosnians and the Croats are forced to flee their homes because of continuing Serbian attacks. Granic invited Demirel to Zagreb and Sarajevo. Demirel, in turn, stated that establishing peace in Bosnia- Herzegovina will prevent the clashes from spreading to Kosovo, Sandzak, Vojvodina, Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia--FYROM], and the rest of the Balkans. Demirel stated that he will be very happy to visit Zagreb and Sarajevo at a [word indistinct] time when he can contribute to the peace process.
